WMS Inspector
======

A Firefox add-on with tools for working with Web Map Services (WMS)

Description
------------

WMS Inspector provides a set of tools for integrators and developers that work
with the Web Map Service (WMS) standard. It aims to ease repetitive tasks like
debugging requests or checking which individual services are used from an
online mapping application. It also focuses on provide a user-friendly output of
the different services' capabilities.

To get more information about the WMS standard visit
http://www.opengeospatial.org/standards/wms

Install
----------
WMS Inspector can be downloaded from addons.mozilla.org (AMO)
http://addons.mozilla.org/addon/wms-inspector/

If you want to install a development version follow this steps:
1.	Clone a git repository from the GitHub repository:
	git://github.com/amercader/WMS-Inspector.git
	or
	Download and extract the source code from
	http://github.com/amercader/WMS-Inspector/archives/master

2.	Locate your Firefox profile folder and open the "extensions" folder
	See http://support.mozilla.com/en-us/kb/Profiles for platform specific
	details.

3.	Create a file named "wmsinspector@flentic.net" and edit it to contain the
	path to the source code you downloaded in the first step, plus the "src"
	folder.

4.	Restart Firefox.

For further details on setting up a development environment for a Firefox
extension, see 
https://developer.mozilla.org/en/Setting_up_extension_development_environment

Support
----------
The discussion list is the place to request support, propose enhancements and 
report bugs.

To subscribe to the discussion list send an email with the subject "subscribe"
to wmsinspector-request@freelists.org
or visit
http://www.freelists.org/list/wmsinspector

To just post a message on the discussion list, send an email to
wmsinspector@freelists.org

